docs.lead_paragraph: In May 1993, as the Clinton Administration struggled to complete its doomed 1,342-page health care proposal, Tennessee's avuncular Democratic Governor, Ned McWherter, cajoled the State Legislature into approving a health care measure of its own. It was a paragraph shy of one and a half pages long.

headline.main: A Managed Care Cure-All With Flaws and Potential
